<text><section>Sec. 31-105. Chauffeur's registration.<section>It shall be unlawful for any person to drive a passenger motor carrier vehicle over any street in Miami-Dade County without first having obtained a chauffeur's registration from the CSD pursuant to, Article V of this Code.</section></section></text><history>(Ord. No. 81-17, § 6, 2-17-81; Ord. No. 87-11, § 2, 3-17-87; Ord. No. 88-118, § 2, 12-6-88; Ord. No. 90-134, § 1, 12-4-90; Ord. No. 91-47, § 1, 4-16-91; Ord. No. 91-125, § 1, 10-15-91; Ord. No. 92-26, § 2, 4-21-92; Ord. No. 94-15, § 3, 1-20-94)</history></law>